Transnet Re-Opens Coal Export Line After 20-Day Shutdown for Maintenance

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-06-13T17:00:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/transnet-re-opens-coal-export-line-after-20-day-shutdown-for-maintenance.html
Transnet Ltd., the state-owned South
African freight rail and ports operator, said it re-opened the
coal export line between Ermelo and  Richards Bay  on June 11
after a 20-day shutdown for maintenance and improvements.  The maintenance will help improve efficiency, the
Johannesburg-based company said in an e-mailed statement today.
The line is railing at full capacity in line with client
contracts, Transnet said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  